==Media==

===Manga===
''Sanrio Boys'' was adapted into two manga adaptations written and illustrated by [[Mai Ando]], with both manga series running concurrently.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/special/48737/|title=ネットで衝撃『サンリオ男子』 老舗キャラ企業が"萌え"に挑む理由|publisher=Oricon|date=2016-03-02|accessdate=2018-02-04}}</ref> {{nihongo|''Sanrio Danshi: Oretachi, Seishun, Hajimemashita.''|サンリオ男子～俺たち、青春、はじめました。～}}, which features the Sanrio Boys' daily lives, was published on the mobile app ''Manga One'' starting April 2016. {{nihongo|''Sanrio Danshi: Oretachi, Koi, Hajimemashita.''|サンリオ男子～俺たち、恋、はじめました。～}}, which features one of the Sanrio Boys being romantically involved with a girl, was serialized in the magazine ''[[Sho-Comi]]'' starting from its June 2016 issue.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/174238|title=「サンリオ男子」がマンガに！4月からマンガワン＆Sho-Comiにて連載開始|publisher=Comic Natalie|date=2016-01-29|accessdate=2018-02-04}}</ref> Both were compiled into volume format and released under the title ''Sanrio Boys'' under [[Shogakukan]]'s ''Flower Comics'' label.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://comics.shogakukan.co.jp/news/870|title=Twitterで超話題『サンリオ男子』コミックス1巻発売!!|publisher=Shogakukan Comics|date=2016-07-22|accessdate=2018-02-04}}</ref>

