{{Infobox ancient site |name = Tash Rabat |native_name = |alternate_name = |image = Tash Rabat in mountains.jpg |alt = |caption = Tash Rabat situated in the surrounding mountains |map_type = Kyrgyzstan |map_alt = |coordinates = {{coord|40.82315|N|75.288766|E|display=inline,title}} |location = [[Naryn Province]], Kyrgyzstan |region = |type = Caravanserai |part_of = |length = |width = |area = |height = |builder = |material = |built = 15th century |abandoned = |epochs = |cultures = |dependency_of = |occupants = |event = |excavations = |archaeologists = |condition = |ownership = Tursun Zhutabaeva (caretaker) |management = |public_access = |notes = }}
'''Tash Rabat''' is a well-preserved 15th century stone [[caravanserai]] in [[At-Bashi District|At Bashy district]], [[Naryn Province]], [[Kyrgyzstan]] located at an altitude of 3,200 meters.
== Geography == Tash Rabat is located somewhat east of the main north-south highway. To the south is Lake [[Chatyr-Kul]] and [[Torugart Pass]]. To the north is [[Koshoy Korgon]], a ruined fortress of uncertain date. The area is a center for hiking and horse-trekking. The caretakers of Tash Rabat offer lodging, consisting of 5 or 6 [[yurt]]s.{{fact|date=February 2017}}
== Research == As early as 1888, Russian doctor and traveler Nicolay Lvovich Zeland suggested that it was originally a [[Nestorian Church|Nestorian]] or [[Buddhist]] [[monastery]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Записки Западно-Сибирского отдела Императорского Русского Географического Общества. Книжка IX. Кашгария и перевалы Тянь-Шаня. Путевые заметки. |trans-title=Notes of the West Siberian division of the Imperial Russian Geographical Society. Book IX. Kashgaria and passes of Tien-Shan. Travel notes. |first=Nicolay |last=Zeland|publisher=Imperial Russian Geographical Society |language=Russian |location=Omsk|year=1888|isbn= |pages=212}}</ref> Research undertaken at the end of the 1970s and beginning of the 1980s by the Institute of History of the [[Kyrgyz Academy of Sciences]] concluded that Tash Rabat was originally built as a Nestorian monastery in the 10th century, although no Christians artifacts were found during excavations.<ref>{{cite journal | last =Khudyakov| first =Ju.| date =| script-title=ru:Таш Рабат - Караван-сарай или замок|trans-title=Tash Rabat - caravanserai or temple.| url =http://ras.ru/FStorage/Download.aspx?id=c7ada38e-692c-436b-8e83-b0bad1c2f759| language =Russian | journal = Priroda | location = | year =2009|issue=6|page=55| publisher= Russian Academy of Sciences| accessdate = 2 May 2014}}</ref>
==Architecture==
The structure consists of 31 rooms, including chambers in the central hall. The rooms are dome-shaped; transition from a quadrangular frame to a dome is done using a [[squinch]]. Tash Rabat is completely made of crushed stone on clay mortar with [[gypsum mortar]] sealing joints.<ref>{{cite book |script-title=ru:Иссык-Куль.Нарын:Энциклопедия |trans-title=Encyclopedia of Issyk-Kul and Naryn Oblasts |first= |last=|publisher=Chief Editorial Board of Kyrgyz Soviet Encyclopedia |language=Russian |location=Bishkek |year=1991 |isbn= 5-89750-009-6 |pages=512}}</ref>
